longBusinessSummary: Dai-ichi Life Holdings, Inc., through its subsidiaries, provides life insurance products in Japan, the United States, and internationally. It operates through The Domestic Life Insurance Business, The Overseas Insurance Business, and Other Business segments. The company offers individual life insurance and annuities, non-participating single premium whole life insurance, financial insurance and annuities, and group annuities. It is also involved in the asset management related business. The company was formerly known as The Dai-Ichi Life Insurance Company, Limited and changed its name to Dai-ichi Life Holdings, Inc. in October 2016. Dai-ichi Life Holdings, Inc. was founded in 1902 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
